Petro-Canada, a state-owned oilcompany, raised the posting prices of sweet and sour crude oils32 cts Canadian per barrel, effective today, the company said.    The change brings the price of light sweet crude to 26.50dlrs Canadian per barrel and the price of light sour crude to23.77 dlrs Canadian a barrel. The crude oils are fromEdmonton/Swann Hills. Reuter&#3;